The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Honda ready to Jazz up small car offer
                                                                                                               Honda ready to Jazz up small car offer
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                          Masahiro Takedagawa (left), Honda Siel Cars India president and CEO, and Fumihiko Ike, CEO of Honda Asia and Oceania operations, in New Delhi on Wednesday. A Telegraph picture                                  
	New Delhi, June 10: Honda Siel Cars India today launched the hatchback Jazz and announced that it would roll out a small car for the Indian market within the next two to three years.        
	A small car is in progress. It will take two to three years. It will be positioned below the Jazz, said Masahiro Takedagawa, president and CEO of Honda Siel Cars India.        
	The small car is likely to be manufactured at the companys second plant, which is under construction in Rajasthan.         
	The engine will be smaller than that of the Jazz, but the exact size and other details such as the cars price will be difficult for us to say right now, said Jnaneshwar Sen, vice-president (marketing) of Honda Siel.        
	The Jazz  known as the Fit in Japan  is priced between Rs 6.98 lakh and Rs 7.33 lakh (ex-showroom, Delhi). The car shares its platform with the City.         
	This is the second generation Jazz. The first generation was launched in 2001 and sold in about 130 countries.         
	The company has sold around 2.8 million units till now.        
	The launch of the Jazz, with a 1.2 litre i-VTEC petrol engine and mileage of 16.1 kilometre per litre, marks Honda Siels entry into the competitive and volume-driven compact-car segment.                                                                                                                                        
